      "content": "# CURRENT STEP SCOPE\n\n**Step 2 of 6**: Fix XPath to filter links containing 'annunci'\n\n## Goal\n## Goal\nModify the XPath in `src/routes.ts` to correctly select only links whose `href` attribute contains the substring \"annunci\", instead of selecting all links with any `href`.\n\n## Task Type\nCode fix in existing scraping logic.\n\n## Technical Context from Codebase\n- **File**: `src/routes.ts`, line 63 (approximately) in the default handler.\n- **Current code**:\n  ```typescript\n  const hrefs = await page.locator('xpath=//a[@href]').evaluateAll(\n      (els) => els.map((el) => (el as unknown as Attr).value),\n  );\n  ```\n- The XPath `//a[@href]` selects **every** `<a>` element that has an `href` attribute, regardless of its value. The subsequent log statement (line 67) incorrectly claims \"Found ${hrefs.length} links containing \\\"annunci\\\"\", but no filtering on \"annunci\" is actually performed.\n- The type cast `(el as unknown as Attr).value` is a separate bug (being fixed in step `fix-type-cast-getattribute`), but the XPath filter must be corrected **now** to ensure the right links are selected once the cast is fixed.\n\n## Action\nModify the XPath in the `page.locator` call to include a predicate that filters for `href` containing the string \"annunci\". Additionally, update the log message to accurately reflect the filtering done.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe current XPath selects all `href`-bearing links, which dilutes the extraction to potentially hundreds of irrelevant links (e.g., navigation, footer). The target use case requires links that point to \"annunci\" (listings/advertisements). By narrowing the XPath, we reduce noise and ensure that only relevant links are considered for further processing. This is the first step in the core extraction fixes; after the type cast bug is resolved, the filtered links will be correctly extracted.\n\n## Implementation Details\n1. Open `src/routes.ts` and locate the line with `'xpath=//a[@href]'` (around line 63).\n2. Change the XPath to: `'xpath=//a[contains(@href, \"annunci\")]'`\n3. Update the log message (likely on the same or next line) from:\n   `context.log.info(`Found ${hrefs.length} links containing \"annunci\"`);`\n   to:\n   `context.log.info(`Found ${hrefs.length} links with href containing \"annunci\"`);`\n4. Keep the existing `evaluateAll` callback as-is (the type cast bug will be fixed separately).\n\n**Important**: Do not change the callback logic (e.g., `.getAttribute('href')`) here – that belongs to the next step.\n\n## Error Handling and Edge Cases\n- If the page contains no links with \"annunci\" in the href, `hrefs` will be an empty array. The log will correctly report 0 links. This is acceptable behavior.\n- If the page structure uses text content or different attribute names (e.g., `data-href`), the XPath filter may miss them. However, the step is specifically about filtering by `href` containing \"annunci\". Future enhancements (like retry with progressive scroll) may address lazy-loaded links.\n- The XPath is case-sensitive. If the target site uses uppercase or mixed-case \"Annunci\", the filter will not match. To account for that, consider using `translate()` or a case-insensitive XPath, but the initial fix should assume lowercase as per the user's context. This can be adjusted later if needed.\n\n## Validation\n- Run the crawler locally against a page known to contain links with \"annunci\" in their href. Example: `npx tsx src/main.ts` with appropriate start URL.\n- Check the log output: it should show a count that is less than or equal to the total number of links on the page.\n- Verify that the extracted `hrefs` array (when the type cast is later fixed) contains only those links whose href includes \"annunci\". For now, the array will still be `undefined` due to the cast bug – that's expected and will be resolved in the next step.\n- If unit or integration tests exist for the route, adjust them to expect the filtered count (or skip them temporarily until the cast fix is merged).\n\n## Dependencies and Inputs\n- This step depends on `debug-current-extraction`, which should have confirmed that the unfiltered XPath extracts many irrelevant links and that the log message is misleading. No other code changes are required before this step.\n- The step `fix-type-cast-getattribute` will follow and fix the `.value` bug to make the extracted hrefs meaningful.\n\n## Constraints\n- Do not modify any other files or add new dependencies.\n- Maintain ESM imports and `.js` extensions if re-exporting.\n- Follow project code conventions (4-space indent, single quotes, Prettier formatting).\n- The change must not introduce TypeScript or lint errors.\n- After the change, the log statement must be truthful about the filtering.\n\nThis is the ONLY task you must complete in this iteration. Do not work on other steps.",
